cs.MA, cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CE

This paper involves optimization and game theory in the context of public transit networks. The use of bilevel programming and the study of both non-adaptive and adaptive passenger behavior suggest a focus on multi-agent systems and game theory, which are covered by cs.MA and cs.GT. The design of exact and approximation algorithms and the use of LP relaxation suggest a focus on optimization, which is covered by cs.LG and cs.RO. Finally, the computational study and the use of local search suggest a focus on computational engineering, which is covered by cs.CE.
